%N A209490 Table T(d,n), read by antidiagonals, gives the number of subsets of length n containing an arithmetic progression of length 3 with distance d.
%C A209490 Offset for n is 3, offset for d is 1, thus 1st entry is T(1,3).
%F A209490 T(d,n) = 2^n - prod_{1=0 to d-1} Tri(floor((n + i)/d) + 2) where Tri(n) is the n-th tribonacci number.
