%e A209490 For T(2,5) we count subsets of {1,...,5} containing {1,3,5}, the only d=2 AP possible here.  There are 4 subsets containing {1,3,5} so T(2,5) = 4.
%t A209490 T[0]=0; T[1] = 1; T[2] = 1;T[n_] := T[n - 1] + T[n - 2] + T[n - 3];a[d_, n_] := 2^n - Product[T[Floor[(n + i)/d] + 2], {i, 0, d - 1}]; Table[a[i, j], {i, 1, 10}, {j, 3, 10}]; Flatten[Table[a[j - i + 1, i + 3], {j, 0, 10}, {i, 0, j}]]
